|kangaroo}}, its Fighting type could also be related to the {{wp|boxing kangaroo}}.\n\nThe shapes of its head and tail resemble that of the armored {{wp|dinosaur}}s \'\'{{wp|Pachycephalosaurus}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Ankylosaurus}}\'\', respectively.\n\n====Name origin====\nBreloom may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|umbrella}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|mushroom}}\'\'. In Latin, \'\'bellum\'\' means \'\'war\'\', perhaps a nod to its Fighting type.\n\nKinogassa may be a combination of 茸 \'\'kinoko\'\' (mushroom) and 笠 {{wp|Kasa (hat)|\'\'kasa\'\'}} or 傘 \'\'kasa\'\' (umbrella). It may also involve a corruption of 衣笠茸 {{wp|Phallus indusiatus|\'\'kinugasatake\'\'}}.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Grass|type2=grass\n|ja=キノガッサ \'\'Kinogassa\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|茸 \'\'kinoko\'\'|mushrooms}} and 笠 {{wp|Kasa (hat)|\'\'kasa\'\'}} or {{tt|傘 \'\'kasa\'\'|umbrella}}, or 衣笠茸 {{wp|Phallus indusiatus|\'\'kinugasatake\'\'}}\n|fr=Chapignon|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|chapeau|hat}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|champignon|mushroom}}\'\'\n|es=Breloom|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Kapilz|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Kappe|cap}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Pilz|mushroom}}\'\'\n|it=Breloom|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=버섯모 \'\'Bosotmo\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|버섯 \'\'beoseot\'\'|mushroom}} and {{tt|모자 \'\'moja\'\'|hat}}\n|zh_cmn=斗笠菇 \'\'Dǒulìgū\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|斗笠 \'\'dǒulì\'\'|bamboo hat}} and {{tt|菇 \'\'gū\'\'|mushroom}}\n|hi=ब्रेलूम \'\'Breloom\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Брелум \'\'Brelum\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=285|prev=Shroomish|nextnum=287|next=Slakoth}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Kapilz]]\n[[es:Breloom]]\n[[fr:Chapignon]]\n[[it:Breloom]]\n[[ja:キノガッサ]]\n[[zh:斗笠菇]]'}